[The number of FMD-vaccine manufacturers in Europe was reduced since
1990, when the EU banned the use of vaccine in member states. This ban
was followed by OIE's establishment of a procedure for the official
recognition of the "FMD free" status of Members, including "freedom
without vaccination." In 1998, the official agreement between the
World Trade Organization (WTO) and the OIE further confirmed the OIE's
mandate to recognise disease-free areas.

Subsequently, a steadily growing number of countries attained the
status "FMD free." However, several major FMD epizootics -- such as
the one in the UK in 2001 and the Japanese and South Korean in 2010,
where mass-culling had to be applied, causing discontent of the public
-- may have provided the background to renewed needs for the vaccine.

A worldwide list of FMD-vaccine producers can be found at
<http://www.cfsph.iastate.edu/IICAB/Vaccines/Disease/diseFMD.htm>; it
would help to check if the said list is updated. - Mod.AS]
